===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|θάλασσα||sea}} (see also {{m|en|thalass-}}) and {{m|en|-emia||blood}} (from {{m|grc|αἷμα}}). The etymology is suggestive of the epidemiology of the disorder, which is more common in people of Mediterranean descent. First used in 1932.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|medicine}} Any of a group of [[inherited]] [[disorder]]s in which the amount of [[hemoglobin]] in the [[blood]] is reduced.

